# ILMU API key (YTL AI Labs Malaysia LLM) — drives /agent endpoint.
# Get one at: https://console.ilmu.ai/dashboard/api-keys
# OpenAI-compatible. Copy this file to backend/.env and fill in.
# backend/.env is gitignored.
ILMU_API_KEY=

# Optional model override. Default = nemo-super (the canonical ILMU model id
# from the custom-api-ilmu-ai provider config). Override only if YTL ships
# additional model ids.
# ILMU_MODEL=nemo-super

# Lock CORS origins. Comma-separated, no trailing slash.
# Default covers localhost dev. Override on Railway/Render with the
# Vercel frontend domain (and any preview URLs you want to allow).
# Local dev:  http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:4173
# Railway:    https://<your-app>.vercel.app
# Multi-env:  https://<your-app>.vercel.app,https://<branch>-<your-app>.vercel.app
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:4173

# Supabase — Phase 1 scoping session storage.
# Project ref: ncpvewfibvjyppoqrcbk. Keys in dashboard → Settings → API.
# Server-side only — never expose SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to the browser.
# Backend falls back to SUPABASE_ANON_KEY if service-role unset (permissive RLS).
# Omit all three → scoping runs stateless (no transcript persistence).
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# Optional: only needed if running backend/migrations/apply.py via psycopg2.
# Otherwise paste 001_scoping.sql into the Supabase SQL editor instead.
# SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Deploy-time vars (Railway / Render dashboard, NOT this file)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PORT — injected automatically by Railway/Render. Do NOT set manually; the
#   Dockerfile binds uvicorn to ${PORT:-8000} via shell expansion.
# Required at deploy: ILMU_API_KEY, CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS, SUPABASE_URL,
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (or SUPABASE_ANON_KEY).
